page.title: 06Ecology-Pamber Forest (ctd.)
page.content: They are not comprehensive but show a resonable cross section of Flora and Fauna currently found in Pamber Forest.{Flora:}Oak,Ash,Sweet Chestnut, Silver Birch,Holly,Wild Cherry,Hazel, Dog Violets,Ladies Smock,Garlic Mustard,Stitchwort,Wild Pansy,Bugle, Speedwell,Wood Sorrel,Foxglove,Early Purple,Spotted,and Butterfly Orchids, Moschatel,Bluebells,Primrose,Spurge, Lily-of-the-Valley,Solomon's Seal,Wood Anemone,Celendines,Pig-Nut and Herb Robert.{Fauna:}Grey Wagtails,Tawny Owls,Redstarts,Tree Creepers,Green, Greater and leoserspotted Woodpeckers, Common Lizard,Adders,Slow Worms,Grey Squirrels,Hedgehogs,Rabbits,Weasels, Stoats,Foxes,Fallow,Roe and Muntjak Deer,Doormice,Butterflies:Purple Emperor,White Admirals,Silver Washed and Pearl Bordered Fritilliaries, Brimstone,Speckled Wood.
